                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d715">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">McCormick</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 19, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. McCormick transmits the reply of the Russian Government to the proposal of
                    the United States relating to the neutrality of China, which states that the
                    Russian Government shares completely the desire to insure tranquillity of China;
                    is ready to adhere to an understanding with other powers for the purpose of
                    safeguarding the neutrality of that Empire on the following conditions: <list>
                        <item>Firstly. China must herself strictly observe all the clauses of
                            neutrality.</item>
                        <item>Secondly. The Japanese Government must loyally observe the engagements
                            entered into with the powers, as well as the principles generally
                            recognized by the law of nations.</item>
                        <item>Thirdly. That it is well understood that neutralization in no case can
                            be extended to Manchuria, the territory of which by the force of events
                            will serve as the field of military operations.)</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
